Q: Elasticsearch replaces scroll for migration A: <p>The new Elasticsearch Java client has a different API for scrolling. You need to use the <strong>scroll()</strong> method, not <strong>search()</strong>, and the builder syntax is different.</p>
<pre class="lang-java prettyprint-override"><code>import co.elastic.clients.elasticsearch.ElasticsearchClient;
import co.elastic.clients.elasticsearch.core.ScrollRequest;
import co.elastic.clients.elasticsearch.core.ScrollResponse;
import co.elastic.clients.elasticsearch._types.Time;

// Continue scroll
ScrollResponse&lt;YourDocumentClass&gt; response = esClient.scroll(s -&gt; s
    .scrollId(previousScrollId)
    .scroll(Time.of(t -&gt; t.time(&quot;60000ms&quot;))),
    YourDocumentClass.class
);
</code></pre>
<p><a href="https://artifacts.elastic.co/javadoc/co/elastic/clients/elasticsearch-java/8.0.1/co/elastic/clients/elasticsearch/core/ScrollResponse.html" rel="nofollow noreferrer">https://artifacts.elastic.co/javadoc/co/elastic/clients/elasticsearch-java/8.0.1/co/elastic/clients/elasticsearch/core/ScrollResponse.html</a></p>

Q: flutter scroll?switch?odometer?digit animation? A: <p>You can use AnimatedSwitcher for this. Example:</p>
<pre><code>AnimatedSwitcher(
  duration: Duration(milliseconds: 300),
  transitionBuilder: (child, animation) {
    return SlideTransition(
      position: Tween&lt;Offset&gt;(
        begin: Offset(0, -1), // comes from top
        end: Offset.zero,
      ).animate(animation),
      child: child,
    );
  },
  child: Text(
    '$_number',
    key: ValueKey(_number), // important - different key for each value
  ),
)
</code></pre>
<p>The key is using <strong>ValueKey</strong> with the number. When the number changes, Flutter treats it as a different widget and triggers the animation.</p>
<p>Change the number directly:</p>
<pre><code>_number = 5; // goes from 1 to 5 directly, won't show 2-3-4
</code></pre>
<p>If you want the old number to slide down, you can add a layoutBuilder, but the above usually works.</p>
